Education Information: Beijing Compresses the Proportion of Junior High School Enrollment of Gifted Students -
On the 21st and 22nd of February, the admission examination of gifted students in junior high schools in Beijing was organized and implemented by the education committees of each district.
This year, each district in Beijing has compressed the proportion of gifted student enrollment, making the competition for gifted students even more intense.
For example, in Dongcheng District, the overall proportion of junior high school enrollment for gifted students from primary schools in the district does not exceed 5% of the total enrollment plan for the district, with a planned enrollment of 380 students, and a school enrollment ratio not exceeding 10% of the school's enrollment plan.
All students who have sports, art, or technology talents and have registered online are eligible to participate in the gifted student enrollment examination.
To facilitate students' participation in the examination, Dongcheng District continues last year's examination arrangement and sets up 1 to 2 examination locations in each school district, a total of 13 examination locations.
The examination points are divided into examination rooms according to the examination area, and time periods are divided into hours. On the day of the examination, students will enter the examination points at different examination rooms in different examination areas according to the time period.
On May 23rd, the district education admission examination center will publicly announce the list of students who have passed the examination on the website, and students can check the examination results online.